  cardName: Convection Elevator
  image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 052ea9ff9e0f47f4d9376588f031f0c6, type: 3}
  fact: Hot air rises, cold air sinks. This is because when the air gets hot, the
    molecules spread out, making it less dense (lighter). This movement of air going
    up and down creates wind!
